Problem in Simple Words
  Move all 0s to the end
  Keep the relative order of non-zero elements
  In-place (no extra array)

Better (Two Pass, In-place)
Idea
  Move all non-zeros to the front
  Fill remaining with zeros

Code:
  void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {
    int index = 0;

    // Move non-zero elements forward
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
        if (nums[i] != 0)
            nums[index++] = nums[i];
    }

    // Fill remaining positions with 0
    while (index < nums.size())
        nums[index++] = 0;
 }

âœ” In-place
âœ” Preserves order
â± O(n)

ðŸŸ© 3ï¸âƒ£ OPTIMAL (Single Pass, Minimal Writes) âœ…ðŸ”¥
ðŸ”‘ Core Idea

Maintain pointers (left,right)
Swap only when needed

âœ… Optimal C++ Code (Interview Favorite)


class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {
        int left = 0;

        for (int right = 0; right < nums.size(); right++) {
            if (nums[right] != 0) {
                swap(nums[right], nums[left]);
                left++;
            }
        }        
    }
};

Complexity
| Type  | Value    |
| ----- | -------- |
| Time  | **O(n)** |
| Space | **O(1)** |
